    <body>
        <%- include('../partials/user/header') %>
<main class="dmf-page">

<section class="hero-section">

  <div class="container">

    <div class="hero-center">

      <span class="eyebrow">
        PATENTED INNOVATION
      </span>


    <div  class="hero-title" >
      <h1 style="opacity: 90%;font-size: 80px;font-family:'Lucida Sans', 'Lucida Sans Regular', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;">
      DMF Technology:
      </h1>
      <div style="opacity: 70%;"> The Future of High-Fidelity Audio Engineering</div>
    </div>


      <p class="hero-description">
        Welcome to a revolutionary breakthrough in acoustic reproduction.
        DMF (Dual Magnetic Field) Technology is a patented next-generation
        speaker motor design engineered to eliminate the physical limitations
        of conventional loudspeakers.
      </p>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="#technology" class="btn-primary">
          Explore Technology
        </a>

        <a href="#visualization" class="btn-secondary">
          Watch Animation
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-stats">

        <div class="stat-card glass">
          <span class="stat-number">2X</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Magnetic Fields</span>
        </div>

        <div class="stat-card glass">
          <span class="stat-number">0%</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Flux Leakage</span>
        </div>

        <div class="stat-card glass">
          <span class="stat-number">MAX</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Efficiency</span>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>

</section>


<section id="technology" class="technology-section">

  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-header">
      <span>THE SCIENCE</span>

      <h2>
        What Is DMF Technology?
      </h2>

      <p>
        A revolutionary approach to magnetic field control.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="technology-grid">
 
<div class="technology-media glass">

  <img
    src="/images/dmfhead.png"
    alt="DMF Technology"
    class="technology-img"
  >

  <div class="glass info-card card-1">
    <h4>Dual Magnetic Field</h4>
    <p>
      Two opposing magnetic systems create a concentrated flux zone.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="glass info-card card-2">
    <h4>Strong Magnetic Gap</h4>
    <p>
      Hyper-dense magnetic energy focused at the center.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="glass info-card card-3">
    <h4>Precision Voice Coil</h4>
    <p>
      Uniform magnetic control across the entire excursion range.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>

      <div class="technology-content">

        <div class="glass content-card">

          <h3>
            The Problem With Traditional Loudspeakers
          </h3>

          <p>
            At the heart of every conventional loudspeaker sits a single
            magnetic circuit driven by one permanent magnet.
            While functional, traditional motor structures inevitably
            suffer from magnetic flux leakage and reduced control over
            the voice coil during extreme excursion.
          </p>

          <p>
            As the cone moves farther from its resting position,
            the voice coil can leave the strongest portion of the magnetic
            field. This results in distortion, reduced efficiency,
            energy loss, and compromised sonic accuracy.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="glass content-card">

          <h3>
            How DMF Changes Everything
          </h3>

          <p>
            DMF Technology completely rewrites the traditional blueprint.
            Instead of relying on a single magnet,
            DMF uses two high-grade permanent magnets positioned with
            identical poles facing one another.
          </p>

          <p>
            Because like poles naturally repel, the two magnetic fields
            compress against each other, forcing magnetic energy into
            a tightly concentrated zone known as the
            <strong>Strong Magnetic Gap.</strong>
          </p>

          <p>
            The voice coil is positioned directly inside this hyper-dense
            magnetic region, allowing it to harness maximum magnetic
            energy with exceptional precision and virtually no wasted force.
          </p>

        </div>

      </div>

    </div>

  </div>

</section>
<section class="breakdown-section">

  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-header">
      <span>HOW IT WORKS</span>

      <h2>
        Engineering The Perfect Magnetic Field
      </h2>

      <p>
        DMF Technology follows a precisely engineered sequence
        that transforms magnetic energy into pure acoustic control.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="breakdown-grid">

      <div class="glass breakdown-card">
        <span class="step">01</span>

        <h3>Dual Magnet Structure</h3>

        <p>
          Two high-grade permanent magnets form the foundation
          of the DMF motor architecture.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="glass breakdown-card">
        <span class="step">02</span>

        <h3>Opposing Alignment</h3>

        <p>
          Identical poles face one another, creating powerful
          magnetic repulsion.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="glass breakdown-card">
        <span class="step">03</span>

        <h3>Flux Compression</h3>

        <p>
          Repelling magnetic fields compress energy into a highly
          concentrated region.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="glass breakdown-card">
        <span class="step">04</span>

        <h3>Strong Magnetic Gap</h3>

        <p>
          The voice coil operates inside a hyper-dense magnetic
